---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { site } from '../../content';
const path = '/alternatives/postscript-alternative';
const title = 'Best Postscript Alternatives for Shopify SMS Marketing in 2026';
const desc = 'Compare Postscript alternatives for Shopify by SMS-native workflows, email depth, consent, message economics, and cross-channel ownership.';
const tools = [
  { name: 'Klaviyo', best: 'Stores coordinating SMS with detailed email and product behavior', pros: 'Rich Shopify events and cross-channel segmentation', cons: 'Profile cost and consent governance grow with complexity', price: 'Verify current contact and feature pricing', source: 'https://www.klaviyo.com/pricing' },
  { name: 'Attentive', best: 'Larger brands with managed SMS acquisition', pros: 'Scale-oriented SMS operations and segmentation', cons: 'Contract and operating model may exceed smaller teams', price: 'Verify current contract pricing', source: 'https://www.attentive.com/pricing' },
  { name: 'Omnisend', best: 'SMB stores wanting bundled email, SMS, and push', pros: 'Fast multichannel ecommerce workflows', cons: 'Frequency and channel economics need monitoring', price: 'Verify current contact and channel pricing', source: 'https://www.omnisend.com/pricing/' },
  { name: 'Brevo', best: 'Teams combining SMS with email and transactional messaging', pros: 'Broad messaging coverage', cons: 'Shopify event depth needs validation', price: 'Verify current send and channel pricing', source: 'https://www.brevo.com/pricing/' },
  { name: 'Sequenzy', best: 'Email lifecycle beside a specialist SMS sender', pros: 'Focused welcome, education, post-purchase, and winback sequences', cons: 'Not a direct SMS replacement', price: 'Verify current plan and integration coverage', source: 'https://sequenzy.io/' },
];
const faqs = [
  { question: 'Why replace Postscript?', answer: 'A store may need deeper email lifecycle, a single data model across channels, a larger managed SMS program, or a broader transactional messaging stack.' },
  { question: 'Can Sequenzy replace Postscript SMS?', answer: 'Treat Sequenzy as a lifecycle-email option unless current SMS capabilities and integrations are explicitly verified. A deliberate Postscript-or-specialist SMS plus Sequenzy email stack may be safer.' },
  { question: 'What should be tested?', answer: 'Test consent, STOP handling, quiet hours, purchase exits, product availability, cross-channel suppression, message costs, and reporting against Shopify orders.' },
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}><ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} /><main class="container py-14 md:py-20"><a href="/alternatives" class="link text-sm">← All alternatives</a><p class="badge mt-6">Shopify SMS migration</p><h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">{title}</h1><p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-orange-950/80">Postscript is SMS-focused. An alternative is justified only when the store needs a different division of labor: deeper email lifecycle, one cross-channel data model, managed enterprise scale, or broader transactional coverage.</p><section class="mt-12 max-w-5xl overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-orange-950/15 bg-white"><table class="w-full text-left"><thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Pros</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{tools.map((tool, i) => <tr class={i === 0 ? 'highlight-row' : ''}><td class="font-semibold">{tool.name}</td><td>{tool.best}</td><td>{tool.pros}</td><td>{tool.cons}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table></section><article class="prose-shopify mt-14 max-w-4xl"><h2>Decide what Postscript is no longer doing</h2><p>Do not migrate simply because another platform has more features. Identify whether the gap is email education, product-event segmentation, SMS scale, transactional separation, or reporting. Then rebuild one complete journey and compare its operational behavior.</p><p>Model message fees, carrier fees, discount depth, opt-outs, complaints, and operator time. Use incremental orders and margin where possible; an attributed revenue total alone does not prove that SMS caused a purchase.</p><h2>Platform notes</h2>{tools.map((tool, i) => <section><h3>{i + 1}. {tool.name}</h3><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {tool.best}. <strong>Pros:</strong> {tool.pros}. <strong>Cons:</strong> {tool.cons}. <strong>Pricing:</strong> {tool.price}. Review the <a href={tool.source} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official source</a> and include message volume, contacts, seats, consent tooling, and integration work.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Consent test</th><td>Can the team prove opt-in, honor STOP, enforce quiet hours, and preserve exclusions?</td></tr><tr><th>Ownership test</th><td>Can the team explain whether SMS, email, or transactional messaging owns each customer state?</td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Migration checklist</h2><ol><li>Export SMS consent, opt-outs, timestamps, source, quiet hours, segments, templates, and flow logic.</li><li>Map Shopify product, cart, order, subscription, and service events to each channel.</li><li>Rebuild cart recovery and test purchase exits, STOP behavior, and out-of-stock suppression.</li><li>Add post-purchase, replenishment, and winback only after cross-channel exclusions work.</li><li>Compare incremental outcomes, margin, opt-outs, complaints, message cost, and repeat quality.</li></ol><h2>Verdict</h2><p>Choose Klaviyo for deep cross-channel behavior, Attentive for managed scale, Omnisend for accessible multichannel operations, Brevo for broad messaging, and Sequenzy when email lifecycle should sit beside a specialist SMS sender. Keep Postscript when SMS-native Shopify execution remains the actual requirement.</p></article><FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="Postscript alternatives FAQ" /><p class="mt-12 text-orange-950/75">Continue with <a class="link" href="/apps">app profiles</a>, <a class="link" href="/compare">comparisons</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides">SMS operator guides</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
